    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cultural Context"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"意 is central to Chinese philosophy and communication. In Confucian thought, understanding\nsomeone's 意 (true intention) is crucial for proper relationships. The concept of 意境 (artistic\nconception) in Chinese arts emphasizes the expression of deep meaning beyond surface\nappearances. 意 represents the bridge between inner thought and outer expression, fundamental to\nChinese concepts of understanding and communication."}],"type":"paragraph"}
